moral_text: He understood that proper procedure required written authorization. He obtained signatures before proceeding.
He felt bound by the severance agreement terms. He returned company property.
He understood that the practice violated antitrust regulations. He ended the price fixing.
He felt bound by the separation agreement. He vacated the premises.
She understood that the practice violated fair housing laws. She removed discriminatory language.
She understood that the practice violated food labeling laws. She listed all allergens.
He felt bound by the supervised visitation order. He remained present throughout.
She understood that the practice violated religious accommodation laws. She adjusted the work schedule.
She understood that the practice violated predatory lending laws. She disclosed all fees clearly.
He understood that the merger would violate competition laws. He abandoned the acquisition.
She understood that policy required proper training. She completed orientation programs.
She understood that the disposal violated hazardous waste laws. She arranged proper treatment.
He felt bound by the terms of his probation. He attended all required meetings.
He understood that proceeding would violate the building setback requirements. He relocated the foundation.
He understood that the disclosure was required by law. He revealed his criminal record.
She understood that the practice violated pyramid scheme laws. She restructured the compensation.
He understood that trading then would violate insider regulations. He canceled his stock order.
She understood that the practice violated educational equity laws. She provided equal resources.
He felt bound by the anti-money laundering rules. He reported the suspicious transaction.
She felt obligated by professional licensing requirements. She displayed her credentials.
He felt bound by the principle of informed consent. He explained all risks before proceeding.
She understood that proper procedure required calibrated instruments. She verified the scale accuracy daily.
He understood that policy required competitive bidding. He solicited multiple quotes.
She understood that the practice violated student privacy laws. She redacted identifying information.
She understood that the practice violated campaign finance laws. She returned the excessive contribution.
She recognized that regulations mandated reporting timelines. She submitted findings within 48 hours.
She recognized that the agreement she signed required her to disclose the information. She told her supervisor about the error.
He felt bound by his obligation to prevent contamination. He sanitized all equipment thoroughly.
She felt constrained by the judicial recusal standards. She withdrew from the case.
She felt obligated by the custody arrangement they had established. She brought the children back on Sunday.
He recognized that the contest rules prohibited multiple entries. He submitted only one application form.
He understood that early release would violate the sentence. He served the full term.
She felt obligated by her promise to keep the secret. She changed the subject when others asked.
She felt constrained by the confidentiality agreement she had signed. She kept the information private.
She understood that modifying the prescription would exceed her authority. She referred the patient to the physician.
She felt obligated by her commitment to maintain accurate records. She corrected the clerical error immediately.
She recognized her responsibility to disclose the conflict of interest. She recused herself from the decision.
She recognized that company policy prohibited personal use of equipment. She printed her resume at the library instead.
She felt obligated by the divorce decree stipulations. She maintained the insurance coverage.
He felt bound by his obligation to maintain patient privacy. He closed the door during the consultation.
She understood that her contract required giving thirty days' notice. She submitted her resignation letter that morning.
She recognized her duty to follow the vaccine storage guidelines. She monitored the temperature logs.
She felt constrained by the medical board regulations. She documented the off-label use.
She felt obligated by the established grievance timeline. She responded within five business days.
He recognized that the regulations prohibited disposing chemicals in regular trash. He used the designated hazardous waste container.
She recognized her responsibility under the lease agreement. She paid the rent by the first.
She felt obligated by the agreed-upon custody arrangement. She brought the children back on Sunday evening.
She recognized that taking credit would violate the agreement made with her colleague. She attributed the idea to her teammate.
He recognized that regulations required licensed operators. He hired only certified personnel.
She felt constrained by the non-solicitation agreement. She avoided recruiting former colleagues.
